result.name: Amber Leaf Restaurant

reviews.text: Reasonable Price with nice service
The full course lunch is fulfilling

A decent fusion restaurant in the middle of Jordan. They've got German, Chinese and Japanese inspired dishes. Prices are okay, in line with other casual diners. Everything tasted pretty good but I thought the roast pork was a bit too salty.

I have dined at this restaurant many times. The menu has great selections of regional Szezhuanese cuisine. The shrimp and fish entries here are incredibly delicious. Price at lunch time is so reasonable that a friend of mine literally comes here everyday. This restaurant is high on my list of "must visit" when you are in the vicinity.
Nice décor, quiet, good price. Good surprise. I will go back.
